Please notice that "watch" variable has no color here:

![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/17722512/19553042/d0ab7f28-96b2-11e6-9057-a3c17ea37ef8.png)
- VSCode Version: 1.6.1
- OS Version: Win 8.1

Steps to Reproduce:

```
// code coloring: with BUG:
var gulp = require('gulp'),
    watch = require('gulp-watch');

// code coloring - OK:
var less = require('gulp-less');
var path = require('path');
```

- VSCode Version: 1.5.2
- OS Version: Windows 8

The command `code --version` does not print to stdout, instead it directly prints to screen. That makes it hard to capture and process the result.

Here is some example code:

```
var exec = require('child_process').exec;

exec('code --version', function (err, stdout, stderr) {
    console.log('stdout: ' + JSON.stringify(stdout));
    console.log('stderr: ' + JSON.stringify(stderr));
});
```

If I run this code then the version number will appear on the console, but the other output channels will be empty:

```
1.5.2 (66f37fd2a99eb9d628dd374d81d78835b410c39b)
stdout: ""
stderr: ""
```
